	   <tr><td colspan=2>Cost about 200 pp on Povar (thats what I paid for mine). I'm impressed with your cloak BTW, +7 wis? &lt;drools&gt;. Anyway other things you should aim for:<br>1) do the Bracer of the Revenent twice (Better ac and +5 wisdom per bracer)<br>2) Get rid of the helmet. Bronze just isn't good enough for the weight cost. Try grouping in Runnyeye for a Blacken Iron Crown (off the King I think), or search the sites for an item that grants you more pluses to stats. You'll soon go into casting more and combat less (more as an aid to the group, and not as a "front line" fighter) While AC is very important, the tanks (War/Rng/Pal/SK) should be taking the majority of the attacks. You'll step in and take some whacks, but not to the extent that you currently do (unless solo'ing)(Note that I'm L30, and still melee, but the beasties rarely focus on me, even with the heals I cast, undeads being the only exceptions.... something about doing 150+ damage per DD undead spell... go figure &lt;grin&gt;)<br>3) Get rid of the face. Yes Agi and Dex are important, but the Silver/Ruby (+4 str +4 wis) and Plat/Ruby (+7 str +7 wis) veils are more important for your later career.<br>4) Testament of Vaniir(sic) a +10 wis held item. Hard to get because of the rotten camp in Highhold pass. Or the Charred Guardian shield (+9 wis and AC...) With Vel and Kunark now out, there's other off-hand held items that you may find easier to get.<br><br>Currently the majority of MY armour is banded with the ad epo's, BI crown, Dwarven ringmail tunic (aka Emp. Crushs' tunic)(25 pp), Barbed Armplates, and splitpaw gloves being the exceptions. You're right at the "money crunch" stage, you'll find that after L24 it eases up. <br><br>Save up for the +wis jewellry items and replace as you can afford them. <br><br>May Brell Guide you to your Reward<br>Durus Stoneguard, Initiate of the 30th mystery of Brell Serilis<br>(Povar Server)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
